# Various interesting quotes. Could be inspirational, educational, whitty/amusing, or generally interesting to read (perhaps in the context of who said it)
+ Investigation of sources (no guarantee nor saying all quotes were verified there): https://quoteinvestigator.com/


>> LIFESTYLE
>> =========

* "The difference between Science and screwing around is writing it down" - Adam Savage

* "First they ignore you. Then they laugh at you. Then they attack you. Then you win." -falsely(?) attributed to Mohandas Gandhi
*   Unverified. Earliest found match is by Nicholas Klein at 1918: "First they ignore you. Then they ridicule you. And then they attack you and want to burn you. And then they build monuments to you."


>> HUMILITY AND TRANSIENCE OF MAN
>> ==============================

* "The greatest problem in communication is the illusion that is has been achieved" - William H. Whyte

* "We play with fire and take the consequences, because the alternative is cowardice in the face of the unknown" - Ronald Dworkin


>> OUTLOOK ON REALITY
>> ==================

* "Quantity has a quality all its own" -falsely attributed to Joseph Stalin
*   Earliest mention found is from Callaghan in writing of: Allied Independence Newsletter No. 13, Naval War College Review, 1979. According to:  https://klangable.com/blog/quantity-has-a-quality-all-its-own/



